    Unrolled.@code_unrolled
    Unrolled.@fixed_range — Macro.

    @fixed_range 3:10 behaves like the standard range 3:10, but is stored within the type system, so that some_tuple[@fixed_range 3:10] is type-stable. Also supports @fixed_range some_tuple[3:end-5] 

    Unrolled.@unroll

    Unrolled.FixedEnd — Type.

    FixedRange{2, FixedEnd()}() behaves like a type-stable 2:end

    Unrolled.FixedRange — Type.

    FixedRange{A, B}() is like UnitRange{Int64}(A, B), but the bounds are encoded in the type.

    Unrolled.function_argument_name — Function.

    function_argument_name(arg_expr)

    Returns the name (as a symbol) of this argument, where arg_expr is whatever can be put in a function definition's argument list (eg. len::Int=5)

    type_length(::Type) returns the length of sequences of that type (only makes sense for sequence-like types, obviously.
